tands right now all items are charged the same point value of .5 with the exception of items dropped off demi/dragon mobs (1) and Leggings (3-5) and BP (4-9)<br>
<br>
As it stands right now the point values for dropped items has no differential means between normal items and really good/uber items. Examples of such are:<br>
<br>
Defiance- 1hs 9/19 +10ac +6str +8dex<br>
Black Blade of Tormenting- 1hs 9/22 eff Tormenting<br>
Jagged Chokdai Spine- Peircing 9/25 +4dex<br>
Argent Defender- 2hs 33/49 +20mana<br>
<br>
All of these items are and have been awarded to members on merit at a .5 value. Why is it that the defiance is a really uber weapon and is charged the same points as the peice of crap Argent Defender.<br>
<br>
Armor is the same way. Pieces dropped from PoH/PoF are marked at the same value as peices dropped from Keal/WW. Why should planes drop armor cost the same as quest armor from Keal. The keal peices are better and are a rarer drop than the planes stuff. Only the BP and Legs are of a higher value<br>
I have emailed our officers about this previously and even proposed a simple easy way to determin point values on a sliding scale according to stats. I am willing to assist (take over if needed) the revamping of points. <br>
<br>
